> Environment Variables 

This project uses environment variables to securely store sensitive configuration such as API endpoints and webhook URLs.

Create a .env file in the root directory and configure it based on the example below.



> API Gateway Endpoint (AWS Lambda URL)
API_URL=https://your-api-id.execute-api.region.amazonaws.com/

> Discord Webhook URL for Alerts
DISCORD_WEBHOOK=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/your-webhook-id

> Environment Mode (optional)
NODE_ENV=production


---

> Explanation of Variables

 API_URL

This is your API Gateway endpoint

Used to send login data from frontend to backend

Replace with your actual AWS API URL



---

> DISCORD_WEBHOOK

This is your Discord webhook URL

Used to send real-time alerts when login is attempted

Keep this private (do NOT expose publicly)



---

> NODE_ENV

Defines environment mode

development → testing

production → live deployment



